  "notes": "Haitian Creole (Kreyòl ayisyen), French-lexifier creole of Haiti, co-official since 1987. The IPN orthography (Institut Pédagogique National, 1979) is strictly phonemic: 32 symbols, no silent letters. ⟨an en on⟩ are the nasal vowels /ã ɛ̃ ɔ̃/ (a following hyphen or an ⟨n⟩+vowel sequence blocks the nasal reading); ⟨ou⟩ = /u/; ⟨r⟩ = /ɣ/. French is the lexifier, not an ancestor node in this graph.",
